      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOME TOWN (5) was in the money two back in a OPEN at Angle Park then jumped from a squeeze draw last time and was not far away when third (16.99) over 300m at this track. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. SHAKA GOES BANG (1) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (23.35) from Box 6 at Gawler. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and two minor placings from 10 starts. Will give a great sight again. AMRON TIGER (7) steps out for the first time at this track. Comes here after a last start 4th and beaten 6 lengths (23.41) at Gawler. Has the ability to give this a shake. ALL THE SASS (2) will be hard to beat with a drop in trip.",
